TOTAL POPULATION - Total population comprises S'pore residents & non-residents.  Resident population comprises S'pore citizens & permanent residents.  Data for 1980 and earlier Censuses refer to all persons present in S'pore on Census day.  Data from 1990 onwards are based on de jure concept.  Data from 2000 onwards are based on the register-based approach.  Data from 2003 onwards exclude residents who are overseas for a continuous period of 12 months or longer as at the reference period.

RESIDENT POPULATION - Data are as at end-June.  Data for 1980 and earlier Censuses refer to all residents (i.e. Singapore citizens and permanent residents) present in Singapore on Census day.  Data from 1990 onwards are based on de jure concept.  Data from 2000 onwards are based on the register-based approach.  Data from 2003 onwards exclude residents who are overseas for a continuous period of 12 months or longer as at the reference period.

SINGAPORE CITIZEN POPULATION - Data are as at end-June.  Data for 1980 and earlier Censuses refer to all citizens present in Singapore on Census day.  Data from 1990 onwards are based on de jure concept.  Data from 2000 onwards are based on the register-based approach.  Data from 2003 onwards exclude citizens who are overseas for a continuous period of 12 months or longer as at the reference period.

PERMANENT RESIDENT POPULATION - Data are as at end-June.  Data for 1980 and earlier Censuses refer to all permanent residents present in Singapore on Census day.  Data from 1990 onwards are based on de jure concept.  Data from 2000 onwards are based on the register-based approach.  Data from 2003 onwards exclude permanent residents who are overseas for a continuous period of 12 months or longer as at the reference period.

NON-RESIDENT POPULATION - Data are as at end-June.  Non-resident population comprises foreigners who were working, studying or living in Singapore but not granted permanent residence, excluding tourists and short-term visitors.

TOTAL POPULATION GROWTH - Total population comprises S'pore residents & non-residents.  Resident population comprises S'pore citizens & permanent residents.  Data for 1980 and earlier Censuses refer to all persons present in Singapore on Census day.  Data from 2003 onwards exclude residents who are overseas for a continuous period of 12 months or longer as at the reference period.  Annual growth rate between 2002 & 2003 are computed based on unrevised population for 2003 which includes residents who are overseas for a continuous period of 12 months or longer as at the reference period.

RESIDENT POPULATION GROWTH - Data are as at end-June.  Data for 1980 and earlier Censuses refer to all residents (i.e. Singapore citizens and permanent residents) present in Singapore on Census day.  Data from 1990 onwards are based on de jure concept.  Data from 2000 onwards are based on the register-based approach.  Data from 2003 onwards exclude residents who are overseas for a continuous period of 12 months or longer as at the reference period.
POPULATION DENSITY - Prior to 2003, data are based on Singapores land area as at end-December.  From 2003 onwards, data are based on Singapores land area as at end-June.
SEX RATIO: MALES PER 1,000 FEMALES - Data for 1970 and from 1980 onwards refer to Singapore residents (citizens and permanent residents).  Data prior to 1980 (except 1970) refer to total population.
MEDIAN AGE OF RESIDENT POPULATION - Data for 1970 and from 1980 onwards refer to Singapore residents (citizens and permanent residents).  Data prior to 1980 (except 1970) refer to total population.

SUPPORT RATIO: PERSONS AGED 15-64 YEARS PER ELDERLY AGED 65 YEARS & OVER - Data for 1970 and from 1980 onwards refer to Singapore residents (citizens and permanent residents).  Data prior to 1980 (except 1970) refer to total population.

SUPPORT RATIO: PERSONS AGED 20-64 YEARS PER ELDERLY AGED 65 YEARS & OVER - Data for 1970 and from 1980 onwards refer to Singapore residents (citizens and permanent residents).  Data prior to 1980 (except 1970) refer to total population.

DEPENDENCY RATIO: PERSONS AGED UNDER 15 YEARS AND 65 YEARS & OVER PER HUNDRED POPULATION AGED 15-64 YEARS - Data for 1970 and from 1980 onwards refer to Singapore residents (citizens and permanent residents).  Data prior to 1980 (except 1970) refer to total population.

DEPENDENCY RATIO: PERSONS AGED UNDER 20 YEARS AND 65 YEARS & OVER PER HUNDRED POPULATION AGED 20-64 YEARS - Data for 1970 and from 1980 onwards refer to Singapore residents (citizens and permanent residents).  Data prior to 1980 (except 1970) refer to total population.

OLD-AGE DEPENDENCY RATIO: PERSONS AGED 65 YEARS & OVER PER HUNDRED POPULATION AGED 20-64 YEARS - Data for 1970 and from 1980 onwards refer to Singapore residents (citizens and permanent residents).  Data prior to 1980 (except 1970) refer to total population.
NATURAL INCREASE - Data pertain to total population.
RATE OF NATURAL INCREASE - Data from 1980 onwards pertain to resident population (i.e. Singapore citizens and permanent residents).  Data prior to 1980 pertain to total population.
